  \label{lem:base_change_mate_fstar_reindex_legs_link_cancelPullbackComp}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.base_change_mate_fstar_reindex_legs_link_cancelPullbackComp}
  \uses{lem:base_change_mate_inner_eCancel_pullbackComp,
        lem:base_change_mate_codomain_read_legs}
  In the reduced form of
  Lemma~\ref{lem:base_change_mate_fstar_reindex_legs_link_cancelEUnit}, the trailing factor
  \(\Gamma\bigl((\operatorname{Spec}\varphi)_{*}(g')_{*}(\mathrm{pullbackComp}_{e,\operatorname{Spec}\iota_A})^{\mathrm{hom}}\bigr)\)
  meets the inverse \((\mathrm{pullbackComp}_{e,\operatorname{Spec}\iota_A})^{\mathrm{inv}}\) baked into
  the leg-rewrite isomorphism \(\mathrm{iso\_g}\) of \(\Theta_{\mathrm{tgt}}\)
  (Lemma~\ref{lem:base_change_mate_codomain_read_legs}). The hom and inverse of one isomorphism
  compose to the identity (Lemma~\ref{lem:base_change_mate_inner_eCancel_pullbackComp}), so the
  comparison composite equals the form with this factor and its matching inverse removed, leaving the
  lone survivor \(\Gamma\bigl((\operatorname{Spec}\varphi)_{*}\eta^{\operatorname{Spec}\iota_A}_{\widetilde M}\bigr)\)
  conjugated by the affine tilde/\(\Gamma\) dictionaries.
\end{lemma}
\begin{proof}
  \uses{lem:base_change_mate_inner_eCancel_pullbackComp,
        lem:base_change_mate_codomain_read_legs}
  Both factors are the hom and inverse of the single isomorphism
  \(\mathrm{pullbackComp}_{e,\operatorname{Spec}\iota_A}\) at \(\widetilde M\), and the codomain read
  is assembled from the same leg factorization, so the inverse it bakes in is exactly this one
  (Lemma~\ref{lem:base_change_mate_codomain_read_legs}). The hom--inverse identity
  (Lemma~\ref{lem:base_change_mate_inner_eCancel_pullbackComp}) collapses the adjacent pair;
  splicing it into the clean composite by congruence and dropping the identity gives the survivor.
\end{proof}

  \label{lem:base_change_mate_fstar_reindex_legs_link_survivor}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.base_change_mate_fstar_reindex_legs_link_survivor}
  \uses{lem:base_change_mate_unit_value, lem:pushforward_spec_tilde_iso,
        def:base_change_mate_inner_value}
  The lone survivor of
  Lemma~\ref{lem:base_change_mate_fstar_reindex_legs_link_cancelPullbackComp} — the affine
  \((\operatorname{Spec}\iota_A)\)-unit \(\eta^{\operatorname{Spec}\iota_A}_{\widetilde M}\) read
  through the affine tilde/\(\Gamma\) dictionaries over \(\operatorname{Spec} A\) and then over
  \(\operatorname{Spec} R\) — equals the canonical \(R\)-linear map
  \(\rho : m \mapsto (1 \otimes 1) \otimes m\) of
  Definition~\ref{def:base_change_mate_inner_value}.
\end{lemma}
\begin{proof}
  \uses{lem:base_change_mate_unit_value, lem:pushforward_spec_tilde_iso,
        def:base_change_mate_inner_value}
  Evaluating the affine unit through the tilde/\(\Gamma\) dictionaries
  (Lemma~\ref{lem:pushforward_spec_tilde_iso}) identifies it with the restriction of scalars along
  \(\varphi\) of the algebraic unit \(\eta_M\), which is Seam~1
  (Lemma~\ref{lem:base_change_mate_unit_value}). Reading it over \(\operatorname{Spec} R\) by
  restriction of scalars along \(\psi\) and the ring equation
  \(\iota_A \circ \varphi = \iota_{R'} \circ \psi\) transports the value onto \(\rho\)
  (Definition~\ref{def:base_change_mate_inner_value}).
\end{proof}

\emph{Step (iii): the mate-unwinding crux, as a chain of clean-term links.} After expanding the
bare \((g')\)-unit (Lemma~\ref{lem:base_change_mate_fstar_reindex_legs_unitExpand}), the comparison
composite is reduced to \(\rho\) by chaining the five clean-term links below. Each is an equality
between two freshly elaborated terms, so the \(\mathcal{O}_X\)-module instance diamond is absent in
its own statement and it is provable by ordinary functoriality / isomorphism cancellation; the
links chain by transitivity of equality:
\begin{enumerate}
  \item \(L_1\) distributes the expanded unit into five \(\Gamma\)-image factors
    (Lemma~\ref{lem:base_change_mate_fstar_reindex_legs_link_distribute});
  \item \(L_2\) collapses the two transparent pushforward-composition factors
    (Lemma~\ref{lem:base_change_mate_fstar_reindex_legs_link_collapseComp});
  \item \(L_3\) cancels the \(e\)-unit factor against the inverse \(e\)-unit baked into the codomain
    read (Lemma~\ref{lem:base_change_mate_fstar_reindex_legs_link_cancelEUnit});
  \item \(L_4\) cancels the trailing \(\mathrm{pullbackComp}\) factor against the inverse built into
    the codomain read
    (Lemma~\ref{lem:base_change_mate_fstar_reindex_legs_link_cancelPullbackComp});
  \item \(L_5\) evaluates the lone surviving affine unit as \(\rho\)
    (Lemma~\ref{lem:base_change_mate_fstar_reindex_legs_link_survivor}).
\end{enumerate}
The transitive composite \(L_1 \cdot L_2 \cdot L_3 \cdot L_4 \cdot L_5\) is the desired identity. A
